        Job Summary:
        Come be a part of what's next! We have 100's of servers to maintain and protect across multiple cloud environments. We're in the process of migrating to the latest and greatest Cloud technologies, while supporting cutting-edge products as well as Big Data analysis and next generation data science in both physical and virtual data centers.
        Invent solutions to continuous integration, continuous deployment (CI/CD) and AWS! Talk about an opportunity to learn and adapt to new challenges! Our goal is total CI/CD from the point of code check-in to deployment to clients, in near-real time. We are inventing and implementing state-of-the-art testing, packaging, and promotion tools and approaches and always pushing boundaries to create a faster and more secure network.
        We are constantly raising the bar of accomplishments and identifying what we need to do to improve, automate and continuously enhance processes, and utilize bleeding edge technology. We are always seeking fresh ideas on what is possible, and need people with the courage and knowledge to commit and deliver in a changing and evolving environment-- all with uncompromising security and world-class service delivery to clients. We achieve this by consistently using critical and logical thinking to perform complete individual tasks, as well as creativity, collaboration and learning to overcome new challenges. Our priority is enhancing our Scrum teams to have the tools and processes to deliver CI/CD into AWS.
        Join us in our passion, taking ownership and continuously learning and improving. Be a part of our growing and winning business in this nationally crucial industry!
        Primary Responsibilities include but are not limited to the following:
        * The Cloud Systems Team is seeking for a talented Junior Database Administrator with at least 2 years of experience in either Microsoft SQL Server or MySQL. Both would be an advantage!
        * This position will perform day to day support and monitoring of our hosted database environments. Tasks include but not limited to do backup maintenance, setting and responding to up DB alerts, monitoring DB instances and replication heartbeats
        * The position also involves interacting with internal customers supporting external customers, corporate and vendor IT staffs to provide world-class production support
        * The position requires creating and maintaining documentation for all of our database environments
        * The position also requires the installation and upgrade of new and existing database platforms including the application of database patching for specific database versions
        * The position will be part of the DB operations team that ensures all database environments are up, running and in optimal condition as part of our SLA agreement with our customers
        * The position will be "on-call" for off-hours support and deployments as needed
        * The position will also be asked to perform DB script deployments as part of our ongoing Change Management Process
