        Basic Qualifications:
        * Bachelor's degree or higher from an accredited university OR minimum of three (3) years of Network experience in lieu of the education requirement
        * Minimum of two or more (2+) years of combined experience in administration for SQL Server and/or MySQL databases
        * Minimum of two or more (2+) years of experience installing and maintaining database environments
        * Minimum of two or more (2+) years of experience in writing, optimizing and deploying SQL scripts
        * Minimum of two or more (2+) years of experience in managing security and access to databases and database environments
        Preferred Qualifications:
        * Graduate technical degree or higher from an accredited university
        * Experience in Scrum/Agile methodology
        * Ability to work with a vibrant team of DBAs, System Administrators and Network Administrators
        * Knowledge of scripting in either Linux or Windows environment
        * Documentation skills and use or tools like Visio, SharePoint, PowerPoint, and Excel.
        * Great communication skills both written and oral
        * Unwavering operations and customer focus.
        * Creative problem solving skills.
        * Ownership of tasks and projects with 100% follow through to completion.
        * Ability to follow process and create process where there is none.
        * Contribute to the overall operational maturity of the team.
        * Experience in handling and securing sensitive information and data
        * Experience in the healthcare field would be advantageous but not required
        * Ability to work after office hours as required for support and deployments
        * Understanding and experience working in cloud systems and virtual machine environments
        * Self-Starter and able to work with minimum supervision
        * Team player
        * Customer centered and service oriented
        Location: REMOTE (NY, NJ, CT, MD, DC, PA, DE, UT, TX preferred)
